/**
 * Measurement harness for the two plan-13 parallelism targets. Every selector uses the same uniform C-intersection-D
 * shape ({@code ?s :p ?left . ?s :q ?right}) and streams the same deterministic result digest. The sequential and
 * concurrent selectors isolate intra-query parallelism with native batching disabled. The serial-batch and
 * parallel-overlap selectors isolate the two currently disjoint dispatch alternatives for the future cost-arbitrated
 * comparison.
 *
 * <p>
 * The default fixture gives both predicates one million statements, exceeding typical L2 capacity while remaining
 * suitable for the single-method benchmark runner. Timing ratios belong in paired JMH evidence, never in this class.
 * Trial setup verifies result parity and query-local execution paths. Under the current complete-group scheduler, a
 * {@code parallelPipelines} path means exactly the configured worker group was admitted; the engagement record exposes
 * that count so an elastic scheduler can replace it with granted-worker telemetry without changing benchmark methods.
 */
